00:02:48.340 --> 00:02:55.810
of what you can use when checking
what plugins you're going

00:02:55.810 --> 00:03:02.400
to use with your WordPress
website or other tools as it were.

00:03:02.400 --> 00:03:06.430
And then I'm going to go
through part A, what's covered

00:03:06.430 --> 00:03:11.600
in part A of ATAG, and I do cover
that a bit more through the slides,

00:03:11.600 --> 00:03:15.500
part B, and then a summary.

00:03:17.600 --> 00:03:21.100
So I'm trying not to give too
much away because I cover most

00:03:21.100 --> 00:03:23.740
of what this all
means as I go through.

00:03:23.740 --> 00:03:29.520
So for the history,
we had ATAG published

00:03:29.520 --> 00:03:36.240
in 2015 after WCAG 2 was released.

00:03:36.240 --> 00:03:44.240
And it goes side by side as
part of the Web Accessibility

00:03:44.310 --> 00:03:48.340
Initiative Guidelines,
because we have three items.

00:03:48.340 --> 00:03:50.440
We've got Web Content
Accessibility Guidelines,

00:03:50.440 --> 00:03:52.660
We've got Authoring Tools
Accessibility Guidelines,

00:03:52.660 --> 00:03:55.420
and User Agent
Accessibility Guidelines.

00:03:55.420 --> 00:03:59.150
They all sort of
intertwine, and both ATAG,

00:03:59.150 --> 00:04:03.990
and I say Ugg rather
than new UAAG sometimes,

00:04:03.990 --> 00:04:08.710
but they both incorporate
WCAG as part of their testing.

00:04:08.710 --> 00:04:12.660
They don't say we're all
independent and repeat stuff.

00:04:12.660 --> 00:04:14.580
They reuse, and that's always
great, isn't it?

00:04:14.580 --> 00:04:17.660
When we reuse each other's items.

00:04:17.660 --> 00:04:19.720
But they have additional checks.

00:04:19.720 --> 00:04:25.700
So authoring tools are things like
WordPress, where it's allowing you

00:04:25.700 --> 00:04:27.670
to create something
that you put online.

00:04:29.500 --> 00:04:32.710
Other tools can we
say, a word processor.

00:04:32.710 --> 00:04:35.610
I'm trying not to name any
companies when I say this,

00:04:37.370 --> 00:04:45.210
or sometimes more complicated tools
that you use to produce a website.

00:04:45.210 --> 00:04:48.930
And again, I'm trying not to mention
Dreamweaver because we all know

00:04:48.930 --> 00:04:52.880
that sometimes the tools don't
always make a good website

00:04:52.880 --> 00:04:55.550
if the author doesn't totally
understand what they're doing.

00:04:55.550 --> 00:04:57.013
And that's why Authoring Tools

00:04:57.014 --> 00:04:59.110
Accessibility Guidelines
were introduced,

00:04:59.110 --> 00:05:02.140
to help you choose the tools
that will help you create

00:05:02.140 --> 00:05:03.140
something accessible.

00:05:04.430 --> 00:05:06.310
And user agent
accessibility guidelines,

00:05:06.310 --> 00:05:11.020
that refers to things like browsers,
and what renders the content.

00:05:11.020 --> 00:05:13.170
We're not going to cover that
too much today, but I want you

00:05:13.170 --> 00:05:15.090
to understand there's
something out there.

00:05:15.090 --> 00:05:20.150
Some say it's no longer needed
because when we get to WCAG3

00:05:20.150 --> 00:05:25.470
and yes, the WC is staying in,
but it's going to be the W3C

00:05:25.470 --> 00:05:28.330
for the acronym rather than
web content because AG is going

00:05:28.330 --> 00:05:34.660
to be accessibility guidelines
for all of these items.

00:05:34.660 --> 00:05:36.560
Anyway, that's still in the future.

00:05:36.560 --> 00:05:43.270
So for now, we have three different
sets that are relevant according

00:05:43.270 --> 00:05:46.150
to what it is you're using.

00:05:46.150 --> 00:05:52.190
And yes,
I did copy an image from the W3C,

00:05:52.190 --> 00:05:55.850
which is why I have credited it so
that you know where I got it from.

00:05:58.440 --> 00:06:04.680
Anyway, the audience for ATAG.

00:06:07.150 --> 00:06:09.360
If you can't make your
website accessible,

00:06:09.360 --> 00:06:12.740
it can mean you exclude a lot
of your potential audience.

00:06:12.740 --> 00:06:15.530
Never assume the needs of the
audience when building a website.

00:06:17.540 --> 00:06:21.190
So the audience of ATAG is designed
for users that create content

00:06:21.190 --> 00:06:23.130
for the web.

00:06:23.130 --> 00:06:26.240
And I do hope a lot of you
are aware of these already,

00:06:26.240 --> 00:06:28.610
but if not,
then this is a great starting point.

00:06:28.610 --> 00:06:35.150
And as I said already, it's used
with WCAG if it's web-based.

00:06:35.150 --> 00:06:39.960
If you've got something that is
an application that doesn't need

00:06:39.960 --> 00:06:44.020
to go online,
then WCAG is not relevant.

00:06:46.230 --> 00:06:48.420
But you still have to make
sure that's accessible to you.

00:06:48.420 --> 00:06:50.130
And it's split into two parts.

00:06:50.130 --> 00:06:53.680
Part A: is the tool
itself accessible?

00:06:53.680 --> 00:06:57.220
If I'm using, say, a screen
reader, do I understand the parts

00:06:57.220 --> 00:07:01.750
of the tool like,
is that button labeled as a button?

00:07:01.750 --> 00:07:07.430
Part B: that's more relevant
to this tool in the fact that

00:07:07.430 --> 00:07:11.350
when you're choosing the tool, does
it let you create accessible content?

00:07:12.410 --> 00:07:17.320
And the reason why these are both
important is because you want

00:07:17.320 --> 00:07:21.480
to use plugins that don't block you
from making your content accessible.

00:07:21.480 --> 00:07:27.420
If you've got something that doesn't
let you put alt tags onto images,

00:07:27.420 --> 00:07:28.910
how's that going to
make your life easier?

00:07:28.910 --> 00:07:32.290
Are you going to add a caption
underneath it in the hope that

00:07:32.290 --> 00:07:33.740
that will be used?

00:07:33.740 --> 00:07:38.320
Or is it going to use AI and
auto-generate alternative text

00:07:38.320 --> 00:07:40.470
that will mean nothing to the user?

00:07:40.470 --> 00:07:44.930
So it's really important to make
sure that if you're choosing a plugin

00:07:44.930 --> 00:07:51.660
to build your site, that you are
going to be allowed to be the author

00:07:51.660 --> 00:07:54.690
of the content and don't let someone
else make the decisions for you.

00:07:55.700 --> 00:07:59.210
Because as we all know,
when it comes to accessibility,

00:07:59.210 --> 00:08:06.240
there's no one size fits all
and we all have like moments...

00:08:06.240 --> 00:08:08.160
I always call it moments
because I have a lot of them.

00:08:08.160 --> 00:08:12.130
I haven't had enough coffee today,
haven't had enough sleep today,

00:08:12.130 --> 00:08:16.780
they kind of go hand in hand really,
or I'm not wearing my glasses,

00:08:16.780 --> 00:08:23.750
or my toddler is pulling at my
arm so I can't type with one hand.

00:08:23.750 --> 00:08:27.540
There's all moments where I need
content to be more accessible,

00:08:27.540 --> 00:08:31.640
so this is why as we all know
it's important we make sure

00:08:31.640 --> 00:08:36.050
what we make is going to
make sure no one's blocked

00:08:36.050 --> 00:08:37.060
by what we deliver.

00:08:38.820 --> 00:08:39.830
So where to start?

00:08:39.830 --> 00:08:41.613
I found this image and I was like,

00:08:41.614 --> 00:08:43.710
that was me trying
to write this talk.

00:08:45.304 --> 00:08:49.010
So I was doing some
research for this talk

00:08:49.010 --> 00:08:55.710
about WordPress accessibility
plugins, and I'll share a bit

00:08:55.710 --> 00:09:00.680
of my findings after
this but when we start,

00:09:00.680 --> 00:09:02.240
do you author the content?

00:09:02.240 --> 00:09:06.630
If you don't, then ATAG might
not be as relevant to you.

00:09:07.860 --> 00:09:14.900
But do you author content,
or do you have a WordPress site

00:09:14.900 --> 00:09:17.200
that you get content
authored for you?

00:09:17.200 --> 00:09:19.790
That's also something
to be aware of.

00:09:19.790 --> 00:09:24.755
Make sure that whatever
plugins you're using are going

00:09:24.756 --> 00:09:26.560
to be meeting ATAG.

00:09:28.630 --> 00:09:29.150
Oh, yes.

00:09:29.150 --> 00:09:30.890
Are you in charge of
selecting the plugins?

00:09:30.890 --> 00:09:31.910
That's always important.

00:09:31.910 --> 00:09:34.830
If not, you can always
highlight to the person that is

00:09:34.830 --> 00:09:40.690
in charge of selecting the
plugins any findings you have,

00:09:40.690 --> 00:09:42.120
with the ones that you use.

00:09:43.480 --> 00:09:47.370
And do you test them to check if they
allow you to add accessible content?

00:09:47.370 --> 00:09:50.890
I've already mentioned the most
obvious one, alternative text.

00:09:52.640 --> 00:09:58.710
But there's other ones too, like
link text, or adding descriptions,

00:09:58.710 --> 00:10:01.350
or hints to items that
might not be intuitive.

00:10:03.330 --> 00:10:05.070
There's so many variations.

00:10:05.070 --> 00:10:06.530
And do they guide you?

00:10:06.530 --> 00:10:12.310
Do they tell you they've
done the work for you?

00:10:12.310 --> 00:10:16.120
Or do they highlight what
might need fixing and help you?

00:10:16.120 --> 00:10:18.740
And do you believe the ones that
claim they do the work for you?

00:10:18.740 --> 00:10:23.140
Because I'm going to share
with you now this website.

00:10:23.140 --> 00:10:26.350
When I was looking into
this, I was looking

00:10:26.350 --> 00:10:33.020
into WordPress accessibility
plugins, and I went through the site.

00:10:33.020 --> 00:10:33.590
I was very excited.

00:10:33.590 --> 00:10:35.760
I was like, oh,
there's like lots of articles.

00:10:35.760 --> 00:10:37.430
And I went through this.

00:10:37.430 --> 00:10:41.750
And I started to go through,
and I started noticing the authors

00:10:41.750 --> 00:10:47.840
that use the way, Accessor B,
there's a lot of plugins that claim

00:10:47.840 --> 00:10:49.220
to do the work for you.

00:10:49.220 --> 00:10:57.220
What they're doing is... Yes,
this article annoyed me quite a bit

00:10:58.660 --> 00:11:04.140
because they're like, oh, I've got
a plug in here and it will fix it

00:11:04.140 --> 00:11:05.230
for you.

00:11:05.230 --> 00:11:09.030
And they don't actually
help you make the choices

00:11:09.030 --> 00:11:14.380
of what changes are made.

00:11:14.380 --> 00:11:16.050
It just overlays it.

00:11:16.050 --> 00:11:20.390
And we all know accessibility
overlays are snake oil.

00:11:20.390 --> 00:11:23.280
They promise to fix things,
but they don't actually

00:11:23.280 --> 00:11:25.280
and they can be
frustrating to users.

00:11:25.280 --> 00:11:28.210
I was looking at a
website the other day.

00:11:28.210 --> 00:11:36.210
I was ordering some bits for my
son who has autism, some light toys

00:11:36.820 --> 00:11:39.070
because he's fascinated by lights.

00:11:39.070 --> 00:11:41.510
And they had an accessibility
plug-in over the top of it

00:11:41.510 --> 00:11:44.390
and it was on my mobile,
and it was blocking my view for part

00:11:44.390 --> 00:11:47.060
of the site because it just wouldn't
go, you couldn't dismiss it.

00:11:47.060 --> 00:11:49.980
And I was like, how's that
actually making my life easier?

00:11:51.400 --> 00:11:52.210
I don't need it.

00:11:52.210 --> 00:11:54.100
I don't want it.

00:11:54.100 --> 00:11:54.730
Go away.

00:11:54.730 --> 00:11:55.640
And I did email them.

00:11:55.640 --> 00:11:56.730
I didn't get a response.

00:11:56.730 --> 00:11:59.870
Just saying, please take it
away, it's not going to work.

00:12:01.040 --> 00:12:04.420
So yes, it does look like,
even though the article

00:12:04.420 --> 00:12:09.310
does recommend Joe Dolsen's plug-in,
that actually looks at the things

00:12:09.310 --> 00:12:12.270
and fixes them to make them
accessible when you start,

00:12:13.360 --> 00:12:15.040
be careful what they promise.

00:12:15.040 --> 00:12:19.980
If they do the hard work for
you, you might end up

00:12:19.980 --> 00:12:25.160
with something that is going to
frustrate and annoy your audience.

00:12:25.160 --> 00:12:30.310
So when it comes to choosing
plugins, go for reputable ones

00:12:30.310 --> 00:12:34.770
and also make sure that they
allow you to make changes,

00:12:34.770 --> 00:12:37.660
that they don't take
the control from you.

00:12:37.660 --> 00:12:42.950
And I think you've shared the
links, haven't you?

00:12:42.950 --> 00:12:49.110
So there's also a lovely overlay
fact sheet that Karl Groves wrote

00:12:49.110 --> 00:12:50.930
and collaborated on.

00:12:50.930 --> 00:12:54.760
And I have signed that,
I think a lot of us probably have.

00:12:54.760 --> 00:12:56.840
I recommend if you
haven't, to sign it.

00:12:56.840 --> 00:12:59.870
Because the overlays are just...
Anyway,

00:12:59.870 --> 00:13:02.370
that was my little soapbox
moment, I apologize there.

00:13:03.390 --> 00:13:06.310
And yes,
that was my frustration there,

00:13:07.500 --> 00:13:13.010
this person's showing their hands
on the head looking at their screen

00:13:13.010 --> 00:13:15.930
when I was looking into these
plugins and finding this article.

00:13:18.280 --> 00:13:25.060
So when it comes to Part B,
which is when you're trying

00:13:25.060 --> 00:13:30.730
to choose the plugin that's right
for you, there's a quick checklist.

00:13:30.730 --> 00:13:32.340
So is there an
accessibility checker?

00:13:32.340 --> 00:13:36.050
I always use that,
I use it on my slides.

00:13:36.050 --> 00:13:39.010
And it's quite clever these
days because it will notice

00:13:39.010 --> 00:13:42.600
if an alternative text has been
generated, and it will say,

00:13:42.600 --> 00:13:43.600
are you sure you want this one?

00:13:44.660 --> 00:13:47.520
Which is good because sometimes
when you look at what is generated,

00:13:47.520 --> 00:13:49.000
it's nothing like the image itself.

00:13:50.170 --> 00:13:53.600
And oh yes, I forgot to say
there's an image of a laptop

00:13:55.720 --> 00:13:57.350
with a WordPress site on it.

00:13:57.350 --> 00:14:02.370
I was quite chuffed when I found
an image of a WordPress site.

00:14:02.370 --> 00:14:07.810
I did have a site once, but I
don't anymore so I apologize there.

00:14:08.950 --> 00:14:11.720
Anyway, so is there an accessibility
checker... Is there something

00:14:11.720 --> 00:14:19.720
that will check my content and flag
anything that maybe needs fixing,

00:14:19.940 --> 00:14:23.210
like color contrast
or is there something

00:14:23.210 --> 00:14:28.680
that doesn't have an alternative text
or... It's always nice to have one.

00:14:28.680 --> 00:14:30.590
If it doesn't have one,
it's not the end of the world

00:14:30.590 --> 00:14:32.770
but it's just good to have.

00:14:33.850 --> 00:14:35.780
What guidance is available?

00:14:35.780 --> 00:14:39.670
Like we all know WordPress is a
