00:34:49.225 --> 00:34:51.360
 <v Joost> Oh, yes,
don't get me started.

00:34:51.360 --> 00:34:53.680
 <v Helen> Yes, anyway.

00:34:53.680 --> 00:34:57.940
 <v Joost> I see a question
from Joe by way of Estella.

00:34:57.940 --> 00:35:01.690
Can you provide a concrete
example of automated content?

00:35:01.690 --> 00:35:05.110
What's a practical scenario
people might encounter

00:35:05.110 --> 00:35:07.530
where automated content
is being created?

00:35:11.081 --> 00:35:12.206
 <v Helen> OK.

00:35:13.770 --> 00:35:18.780
If you use Word and
you paste in an image,

00:35:19.930 --> 00:35:23.690
it will generate
alternative text and it has

00:35:23.690 --> 00:35:29.000
a sentence underneath it
saying, auto generated content.

00:35:29.000 --> 00:35:31.930
And then that gets flagged
in the accessibility checker

00:35:31.930 --> 00:35:34.470
because that's a phrase
it looks for to make sure

00:35:34.470 --> 00:35:39.040
that you've checked that the
alternative text is valid.

00:35:39.040 --> 00:35:43.500
That's great because it not
only tells you what it does,

00:35:43.500 --> 00:35:50.420
that it's done the alternative
text, but it also trying.

00:35:50.420 --> 00:35:55.240
So those are the automated
content that's being created.

00:35:57.210 --> 00:36:01.220
And like Facebook, again,
it does say, might be.

00:36:01.220 --> 00:36:02.390
It never says it definitely is.

00:36:02.390 --> 00:36:06.530
It will say, could be this,
because it knows it might be wrong.

00:36:06.530 --> 00:36:11.590
But not everyone will know that
something has been automated

00:36:11.590 --> 00:36:16.130
because not all tools will do
that in an easy to spot way.

00:36:17.180 --> 00:36:21.180
So if you've got a tool that
generates alternative text

00:36:21.180 --> 00:36:24.950
that you haven't created, it wasn't
from the original source file,

00:36:24.950 --> 00:36:29.380
and it's incorrect, then it's
going to make you look a bit

00:36:29.380 --> 00:36:33.080
of a [Inaudible 36:30]

00:36:33.080 --> 00:36:35.750
for not having the right term
in your alternative text.

00:36:35.750 --> 00:36:39.880
So that's something that I
recommend checking in your plugins.

00:36:39.880 --> 00:36:45.060
If it does the AI side of things,
does it make it easy for you

00:36:45.060 --> 00:36:46.050
to spot it has done it?

