00:37:51.280 --> 00:37:54.690
 <v Helen> Ask the
community, as a first point.

00:37:54.690 --> 00:38:00.980
And also check the company that
makes it, because I instantly knew

00:38:00.980 --> 00:38:06.360
when I see a Accessaby or
just looking at the list now

00:38:06.360 --> 00:38:09.280
that I got open here.

00:38:09.280 --> 00:38:12.150
So when you go through the
list and you see a company name

00:38:12.150 --> 00:38:16.340
that you know is an overlay
provider, like Userway,

00:38:16.340 --> 00:38:21.160
that tells me don't use
it, it's going to enforce

00:38:21.160 --> 00:38:27.540
what it thinks should be done,
or is programmed should be done.

00:38:27.540 --> 00:38:32.380
I should never blame the actual
tool itself because it's only

00:38:32.380 --> 00:38:35.760
as good as a program that makes
it and it's best intentions,

00:38:35.760 --> 00:38:37.710
but yes anyway.

00:38:39.560 --> 00:38:41.850
But also,
when I go through the descriptions,

00:38:41.850 --> 00:38:49.850
if I see something like it's paid
for, it will change items for you.

00:38:50.910 --> 00:38:53.710
You don't have to do any
of the work yourself.

00:38:54.730 --> 00:38:58.410
That’s a snake oil bit,
that's a bit that everyone goes for

00:38:58.410 --> 00:39:05.500
because it's telling you
exactly the easy route.

00:39:05.500 --> 00:39:11.570
If it's too easy, then you're
not able to change it yourself,

00:39:11.570 --> 00:39:14.110
and then that means you
can be producing complete

00:39:15.490 --> 00:39:18.960
insert rude words there,
rather than something that's going

00:39:18.960 --> 00:39:20.020
to help your audience.

00:39:21.900 --> 00:39:25.780
 <v Joost> Yes, if it sounds too
