00:42:13.430 --> 00:42:19.690
Because your mobile app is the user
agent that's rendering the content.

00:42:19.690 --> 00:42:24.090
So it's still available online, but
it's not in the recognized browser.

00:42:25.520 --> 00:42:29.308
So yes, it's not always
one-size-fits-all,

00:42:29.309 --> 00:42:31.950
but understanding that you're

00:42:31.950 --> 00:42:36.090
on the developer side, you're the
creator and the tools you need,

00:42:36.090 --> 00:42:36.670
need ATAG.

